"The President has been kidnapped by Ninjas! Are you a bad enough dude to rescue the president?"<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#aaaaaa><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub89.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Moderator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>2/21/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>9:06:47 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Cheesy graphics killed the video game star.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hmm, I love my 2d games, and have been getting into a lot of older games again lately, but I still love some 3d ones just as much. I've got to admit, I like Tomb Raider. Now I won't argue that it hasn't become repetitive and is sold a lot by the &quot;sex appeal&quot;, but I don't care about all that. For one thing, Lara Croft is not sexy, no matter how badly Eidos wants to believe she is. If a real woman looked like her she definitely wouldn't be considered sexy. I loved the original game, and at the time it was just that: original. I still played all the other games, because I like that kind of game. You could say Mega Man was just as repetitive, you do pretty much the same thing each game, just with different graphics and levels. I don't care. If the games good to me, I don't really care if it's basically the same thing. Now, I'm all for originality or they wouldn't have been made in the first place, but if a game's fun I like it. Tomb Raider to me is basically the same game with a bunch of add on levels each year, but I still like it. Hopefully with the new TR for PS2 the gameplay and graphics will evolve some, which it seems they have from what I've seen. Hey, you never know, in this one Laura might even look part human!</font><P>Thomas Bonvillain<br>
