<embed src="http://www.undeadart.com/temp/flashsig.swf"  width="180" height="60"><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uthedogfuchow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Dogfuchow</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.isophalence.net/akbhar/1.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Member</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>2/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>5:35:02 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.isophalence.net/akbhar/icons/monk5.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Castlevania-returns!!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Metroid FPS? HAHAHH! That's gonna suck!</font><P>"Put your hands down! For God's sake put 'em down! NOW!<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#aaaaaa><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=renaissanceman>Renaissance Man</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://fp.geocities.com/sche0487/3dwalls_icon.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Karbonite</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>3/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>3:26:22 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Video game discussion I missed out on</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This has been a very interesting discussion of the different aspects of video game evolution. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I think it's important to realize that the reason they made 2D games in the past is because that's all they really could do.  As the systems became more powerful, they were able to make better and better 2D games.  I remember well the impact Super Mario World had on me all those years ago.  Super Metroid also stands out strongly in my mind as a major 2D milestone.  Now that it is possible to make 3D games, I believe that is the direction we must go.  The frontiers of 2D gaming have already pushed about as far as they can go.  We still need to pay homage to the past, but we mustn't wallow in mindless nostalgia.  Of course, I still love the classics, and I am dismayed to hear that Metroid might be implemented as a 3D game in this way.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I do believe there is still some room for original 2D games on the new systems.  The level of detail and speed they could have put into a 2D version of Metroid on the gamecube are tough to imagine.  It would probably be faster than a normal human's reaction time.  But then us gamers aren't normal humans, are we? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Moderator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>3/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#336699>3:43:59 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Video game discussion I missed out on</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I agree that we should continue to develop 3d games, but that doesn't mean that's all developers have to make. Just because you can do something, doesn't mean you have to. I love 3d games, and I also love 3d games. There are certain things you can do that is better suited to each. And it is not true that 2d games have been pushed as far as they can. With most systems using DVD now, which has MUCH more space than CD's, there is so much more we can do. That means higher res graphics and more of them. Just as 3d is approaching realism, 2d is approaching full length animation quality games. I don't think we should stop making 2d games just because we can make things 3d. I think a balance would be a better approach.</font><P><embed src="http://www.undeadart.com/temp/flashsig.swf"  width="180" height="60">
